ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC NETDRAW options ; 
    ACTNET / options ;

The NETDRAW procedure draws a network diagram of the activities in a project. Boxes (or nodes) are used to represent
the activities, and lines (or arcs) are used to show the precedence relationships among the activities.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: ACTNET / options ; 

The ACTNET statement draws the network diagram. You can specify several options in this 
statement to control the appearance of the network.
